        <title>Implement PWA caching using workbox</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://supersubwoofer.github.io/myblog/hnpwa/&quot;&gt;DEMO&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;notes-on-studying-and-implement-pwa&quot;&gt;Notes on studying and implement PWA&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;web-app-should-be-accessible-responsive-and-progressive&quot;&gt;Web app should be accessible, responsive and Progressive&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;major-benefits-of-pwa&quot;&gt;Major benefits of PWA&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Provides similar user experience to native app&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Can be distributed without application store&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Better user adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;pwa-implementation---the-prpl-pattern&quot;&gt;PWA implementation - the PRPL pattern&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Push critical resources for the initial URL route&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Render initial route&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Pre-cache remaining routes&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Lazy-load and create remaining routes on demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;experiment&quot;&gt;Experiment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Implement Hacker News reader as a PWA. Using &lt;a href=&quot;https://developers.google.com/web/tools/workbox/&quot;&gt;Workbox&lt;/a&gt; to precache app-shell, precache static assets and cache network response. Here is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://supersubwoofer.github.io/myblog/hnpwa/&quot;&gt;DEMO&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

